examples.en: I think that you're being unfair.
It was monstrously unfair.
It is unfair of a man to compare his wife with his mother.
It's unfair to punish a whole class for the actions of one or two students.
He made a very unfair crack about her looks.
He argued that the reproaches were unfair.
Many big firms freeze out their rivals by unfair means.
Our research led us to the conclusion that the present system is unfair.
She protested that the law was unfair.
The maximum award for unfair dismissal is 55,000.
He lost his claim for unfair dismissal.
Aren't you being a little bit unfair?
It's unfair for them to be allowed to leave early if we can't.
Companies that receive government subsidies have an unfair advantage.
The unfair tax laws sparked a rebellion.
It seems unfair to single her out for criticism.
Mr. Chairman, I object. That is an unfair allegation.
The company has been accused of unfair labor practices.
He has an unfair advantage over us because of his wealth.
The council was slammed for its unfair selection procedure.
Wartime hysteria led to many unfair accusations of treachery.
Voters tend to identify the Party with unfair treatment of the poor.
The U.S. Congress can abrogate old treaties that are unfair to Native Americans.
The accusation of elitism seems unfair as the festival presents a wide range of music, with something to please everyone.
